}

4 Population variability
Drawing 500 virtual subjects’ random effects from the estimated ω matrix shows the spread of real-world exposures, not just the average. For a narrow-therapeutic- index drug like theophylline, this band is what matters — it indicates how many patients might stray outside the therapeutic window on a given dose.


